The paper deals with the use of deep neural networks for automated personality attribution, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The study also involves analyzing the performance of the models, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper addresses the impact of context on personality attribution, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and multimedia (cs.MM).
